{"TopicId":37036,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"eccentricity info","CreatedByName":"coconuttree","CreatedById":58721,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-14T16:19:54Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"coconuttree","CreatedById":58721,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-14T16:19:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Ehow do you view eccentricity of your orbit?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gojira","CreatedById":10884,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-14T16:27:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI think you have to calculate it. You could always get a plugin like Mechjeb or something that displays orbital information.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"stupid_chris","CreatedById":62017,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-14T16:42:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIndeed, that kind of info isn\u0027t given in the stock game.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"coconuttree","CreatedById":58721,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-15T00:16:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Eoh. i have been watching duncan, from the yogscast, and in one of his episodes, i saw an eccentricity calculator of sorts. so i was wondering whether the eccentricity was bound to a key or something.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ComradeGoat","CreatedById":59041,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-15T00:45:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EKerbal Engineer Redux displays various orbital parameters, including eccentricity. I never leave home without it!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"alterbaron","CreatedById":57492,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-15T01:51:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIt\u0027s easy to calculate the eccentricity from the apoapsis and periapsis distances:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/math/6/b/6/6b6d8b62814b56a3bad2a83aad6b2195.png\u0022 alt=\u00226b6d8b62814b56a3bad2a83aad6b2195.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EJust remember that you have to add the planet\u0027s radius to your AP and PE altitudes.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nuges","CreatedById":190250,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-05T15:01:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u0022511651\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002237036\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221373853073\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257492\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alterbaron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/15/2013 at 2:51 AM, alterbaron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s easy to calculate the eccentricity from the apoapsis and periapsis distances:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00226b6d8b62814b56a3bad2a83aad6b2195.png\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/math/6/b/6/6b6d8b62814b56a3bad2a83aad6b2195.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust remember that you have to add the planet\u0027s radius to your AP and PE altitudes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom your formula, as apoapsis and periapsis get closer to each other the eccentricity tends to zero (0). I tried it on the game and it works, I have a circular orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-05T21:09:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223410810\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002237036\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221530802865\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190250\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nuges\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Nuges said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom your formula, as apoapsis and periapsis get closer to each other the eccentricity tends to zero (0). I tried it on the game and it works, I have a circular orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E has not been on the forum for quite some time, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/190250-nuges/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022190250\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/190250-nuges/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nuges\u003C/a\u003E, but it was nice of you to offer help. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}